#. [topic]: id=arkan_thoria
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:26
msgid "Arkan-thoria"
msgstr "Arcan-doria"

#. [topic]: id=arkan_thoria
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:27
msgid ""
"A river rising in the <ref dst='heart_mountains'>Heart Mountains</ref> and "
"running east to the Listra."
msgstr ""
"Río que nace nas <ref dst='heart_mountains'>Montañas Profundas'</ref> e flúe "
"cara o leste ata desaugar no Listra."

#. [topic]: id=great_river
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:32
msgid "Great River"
msgstr "Gran Río"

#. [topic]: id=great_river
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:33
msgid ""
"The Great River forms the boundary between the <ref "
"dst='kingdom_wesnoth'>Kingdom of Wesnoth</ref> and the <ref "
"dst='northlands'>Northlands</ref>. It empties to the <ref "
"dst='great_ocean'>ocean</ref> at <ref dst='elensefar'>Elensefar</ref>."
msgstr ""
"O Gran Río forma a fronteira entre o <ref dst='kingdom_wesnoth'>Reino de "
"Wesnoth</ref> e as <ref dst='northlands'>Terras do Norte</ref>. Desemboca no "
"<ref dst='great_ocean'>océano</ref> en <ref dst='elensefar'>Elensefar</ref>."

#. [topic]: id=great_river
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:35
msgid ""
"The Ford of Abez is a crossing between Wesnoth and the Northlands, and is "
"the westernmost point where the Great River can be crossed without ships."
msgstr ""
"O Vao de Abez é un punto de paso entre o Noroeste e as Terras do Norte, e é "
"o lugar máis occidental onde se pode cruzar o Gran Río sen necesidade de "
"barcos."

#. [topic]: id=great_ocean
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:40
msgid "Great Ocean"
msgstr "Gran Océano"

#. [topic]: id=great_ocean
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:41
msgid ""
"Lies to the west of the <ref dst='great_continent'>continent</ref> and all "
"rivers eventually flow to it. Far to the west in the Great Ocean is a huge "
"archipelago called <ref dst='morogor'>Morogor</ref>."
msgstr ""
"Situado ao oeste do <ref dst='great_continent'>Gran Continente</ref>, a el "
"van parar todos os ríos. No distante oeste do gran océano hai un extenso "
"arquipélago que recibe o nome de <ref dst='morogor'>Mórogor</ref>."

#. [topic]: id=great_ocean
#. Great Ocean
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:45
msgid ""
"The Drakes once called this ocean the World Ocean. They believe it to extend "
"in every direction from Morogor until eventually flowing into the abyss as "
"an immense waterfall at the edge of the world."
msgstr ""
"Os Draconiáns chamaron a este océano, noutro tempo, o Océano Mundial. Eles "
"cren que se estende en todas as direccións desde Morogor ata acabar fluíndo "
"ao abismo como unha inmensa fervenza na beira do mundo."

#. [topic]: id=morogor
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:50
msgid "Morogor"
msgstr "Mórogor"

#. [topic]: id=morogor
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:51
msgid ""
"Archipelago, located somewhere in the <ref dst='great_ocean'>Great Ocean</"
"ref> east of the <ref dst='green_isle'>Green Isle</ref> and west of the <ref "
"dst='great_continent'>Great Continent</ref>.\n"
"It is mostly inhabited by <ref dst='..race_drake'>drakes</ref>.\n"
"The central island of the archipelago is also called ‘Morogor’."
msgstr ""
"Arquipélago situado nalgunha parte do <ref dst='great_ocean'>Gran Océano</"
"ref>, ao oeste da <ref dst='green_isle'>Illa Verde</ref> e ao leste do <ref "
"dst='great_continent'>Gran Continente'</ref>.\n"
"Está habitado principalmente por <ref dst='..race_drake'>draconiáns'</ref>.\n"
"A illa central do arquipélago tamén se chama ‘Morogor’."

#. [topic]: id=morogor
#. Geography of Morogor
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:57
msgid ""
"<header>Notable land features:</header>\n"
"    • Mount Morogor: The highest active volcanic mountain in the central "
"island of Morogor.\n"
"    • Isle of Gaall: A dangerous island slightly north of the central Isle "
"of Morogor, used mostly as hunting ground by the drakes, who inhabit only "
"two small villages on the isle.\n"
"    • Isle of Omarath: A major drakish island northwest of the main Isle of "
"Morogor. It is the northernmost island of the Morogor Archipelago."
msgstr ""
"<header>Características terrestres notables:</header>\n"
"• Monte Morogor: A montaña volcánica activa máis alta da illa central de "
"Morogor.\n"
"• Illa de Gaall: Unha illa perigosa lixeiramente ao norte da illa central de "
"Morogor, utilizada principalmente como terreo de caza polos dragóns, que "
"habitan só dúas pequenas aldeas na illa.\n"
"• Illa de Omarath: Unha importante illa draco ao noroeste da illa principal "
"de Morogor. É a illa máis setentrional do arquipélago de Morogor."

#. [topic]: id=green_isle
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:65
msgid "Green Isle"
msgstr "Illa Verde"

#. [topic]: id=green_isle
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:66
msgid ""
"A bigger island lying in the <ref dst='great_ocean'>Great Ocean</ref>, "
"formerly home to the Islefolk and Wesfolk."
msgstr ""
"A illa máis grande do <ref dst='great_ocean'>Gran Océano</ref>, "
"anteriormente fogar da xente das illas e dos pobos do oeste."

#. [topic]: id=green_isle
#. Geography of the Green Isle
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:70
msgid ""
"<header>Notable cities:</header>\n"
"    • Southbay: The capital of the largest Islefolk kingdom.\n"
"    • Clearwater Port: The second largest Islefolk city and the location of "
"a major port.\n"
"    • Stormvale: A major Islefolk kingdom once ruled by the ancestors of "
"Haldric I.\n"
"    • Jevyan’s Haven: The Wesfolk capital and home of the famous lich-lord "
"Jevyan.\n"
"    • Blackmore: A small settlement north of the Oldwood."
msgstr ""
"<header>Cidades notables:</header>\n"
"• Southbay: A capital do maior reino da xente das illas.\n"
"• Porto de Clearwater: A segunda cidade máis grande da xente das illas e a "
"localización dun porto importante.\n"
"• Stormvale: Un importante reino da xente das illas que outrora gobernado "
"polos antepasados de Haldric I.\n"
"• Refuxio de Jevyan: A capital da xente das illas e fogar do famoso señor "
"lich Jevyan.\n"
"• Blackmore: Un pequeno asentamento ao norte do Bosque Vello."

#. [topic]: id=green_isle
#. Geography of the Green Isle
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:79
msgid ""
"<header>Notable land features:</header>\n"
"    • Broken Mountains: A mighty mountain range that cuts through the Green "
"Isle.\n"
"    • Midlands: A hilly and sparsely forested area south of the Swamp of "
"Esten, once home to prosperous Islefolk kingdoms.\n"
"    • Oldwood: A mysterious wood inhabited by some ancient woses. Dark old "
"catacombs are located below a temple in the heart of the forest.\n"
"    • Swamp of Esten: A small swamp located east of the Broken Mountains "
"once home to Wesfolk-imitating cultists. The swamp was defiled in wars "
"between Wesfolk and Islefolk long ago."
msgstr ""
"<header>Características terrestres notables:</header>\n"
"• Montañas Quebradas: Unha poderosa cadea montañosa que atravesa a Illa "
"Verde.\n"
"• Terras medias: Unha zona de outeiros pouco boscosa ao sur do Pantano de "
"Esten, outrora fogar de prósperos reinos da xente da Illa.\n"
"• Bosque Vello: Un misterioso bosque habitado por algúns antigos woses. As "
"antigas catacumbas escuras están situadas debaixo dun templo no corazón do "
"bosque.\n"
"• Pantano de Esten: Un pequeno pantano situado ao leste das Montañas "
"Quebradas, outrora fogar de seareiros que imitaban á xente do Oeste. O "
"pantano foi profanado hai tempo en guerras entre a xente do Oeste e a xente "
"da Illa."

#. [topic]: id=old_continent
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:88
msgid "Old Continent"
msgstr "Vello Continente"

#. [topic]: id=old_continent
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:89
msgid ""
"Lies to the west of <ref dst='morogor'>Morogor</ref> and the <ref "
"dst='green_isle'>Green Isle</ref> across the <ref dst='great_ocean'>Great "
"Ocean</ref>. It is the original homeland of both humans and orcs."
msgstr ""
"Atópase ao oeste de <ref dst='morogor'>Morogor</ref> e da <ref "
"dst='green_isle'>Illa Verde</ref>, ao outro lado do <ref "
"dst='great_ocean'>Gran Océano</ref>. É a patria orixinal tanto dos humanos "
"como dos orcos."

#. [topic]: id=great_continent
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:94
msgid "Great Continent"
msgstr "Gran Continente"

#. [topic]: id=great_continent
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:95
msgid ""
"The continent on which the <ref dst='kingdom_wesnoth'>Kingdom of Wesnoth</"
"ref> lies. Its west coast is surrounded by the <ref dst='great_ocean'>Great "
"Ocean</ref>."
msgstr ""
"Continente no que se estableceu o <ref dst='kingdom_wesnoth'>Reino do "
"Noroeste'</ref>. O <ref dst='great_ocean'>Gran Océano'</ref> baña a súa "
"costa oeste."

#. [topic]: id=irdya
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:100
msgid "Irdya"
msgstr "Irïdia"

#. [topic]: id=irdya
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:101
msgid ""
"The name of the world in which the kingdom of <ref "
"dst='kingdom_wesnoth'>Wesnoth</ref> is situated is ‘Irdya’. This term is, "
"however, only rarely used in the era depicted by the main map. People "
"normally just say “the world” or, poetically, “the wide green world”."
msgstr ""
"O nome do mundo no que está o <ref dst='kingdom_wesnoth'>Noroeste'</ref> "
"chámase «Iridia».Porén, este termo úsase só raramente na era representada "
"polo mapa principal. A xente normalmente refírese a el simplemente como “o "
"mundo” ou, de forma poética, “o amplo mundo verde”."

#. [topic]: id=kingdom_wesnoth
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:106
msgid "Kingdom of Wesnoth"
msgstr "Reino do Noroeste"

#. [topic]: id=kingdom_wesnoth
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:107
msgid ""
"The Kingdom of Wesnoth is located in the north-central portion of the <ref "
"dst='great_continent'>Great Continent</ref>. Most of the mainline campaigns "
"revolve around it. It is bounded on the map by the <ref "
"dst='great_river'>Great River</ref> to the north, the shore of the <ref "
"dst='great_ocean'>ocean</ref> to the west, the Aethenwood to the <ref "
"dst='southwest_elven_lands'>southwest</ref>, and the Bitter Swamp to the "
"southeast.\n"
"\n"
"Over the River Aethen, south of Fort Tahn, is a Wesnothian frontier region. "
"It is bounded to the south by dense woods of which the Aethenwood may be "
"considered a northernmost extension. Kerlath is its southernmost province, "
"marking the end of Wesnoth and the start of the mysterious <ref "
"dst='far_south'>Far South</ref>."
msgstr ""
"O Reino do Noroeste está situado na parte centro-norte do <ref "
"dst='great_continent'>Gran Continente</ref>. A maioría das campañas "
"principais xiran arredor del. Está delimitado no mapa polo <ref "
"dst='great_river'>Gran Río</ref> ao norte, a ribeira do <ref "
"dst='great_ocean'>océano</ref> ao oeste, a fraga de Aethen ao <ref "
"dst='southwest_elven_lands'>suroeste</ref> e o Pantano Amargo ao sueste.\n"
"\n"
"Sobre o río Aethen, ao sur de Fort Tahn, atópase unha rexión fronteiriza do "
"Noroeste. Está delimitada ao sur por densas fragas das cales a fraga de "
"Aethen pode considerarse unha extensión máis setentrional. Kerlath é a súa "
"provincia máis meridional, marcando o final do Noroeste e o comezo do "
"misterioso <ref dst='far_south'>Lonxano Sur</ref>."

#. [topic]: id=kingdom_wesnoth
#. Geography of Wesnoth
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:113
msgid ""
"<header>Notable cities:</header>\n"
"    • Weldyn: The capital of Wesnoth.\n"
"    • Aldril: City lying on the Bay of Pearls.\n"
"    • Blackwater Port: City lying south of the Bay of Pearls.\n"
"    • Carcyn: Located between the Grey Woods and the Great River.\n"
"    • Dan’Tonk: Wesnoth’s largest city, located in the center of the "
"country, just west and north of Weldyn.\n"
"    • Soradoc: The easternmost town of Wesnoth, controls the confluence of "
"the Weldyn River and the Great River.\n"
"    • Fort Tahn: The southernmost border outpost, controls the north/south "
"road crossing the River Aethen.\n"
"    • Tath: Important fort city north of Dan’Tonk, exerts control over the "
"wilderness country around the east of the Brown Hills and north to the Ford "
"of Abez.\n"
"    • Westin: A small yet important town in Kerlath, the southernmost "
"province of Wesnoth. The old Citadel of Westin can be found there.\n"
"    • Southport: A small town in the southernmost reaches of Kerlath, near "
"the Black Forest."
msgstr ""
"<header>Cidades notables:</header>\n"
"• Weldyn: A capital de Wesnoth.\n"
"• Aldril: Cidade situada na Baía das Pérolas.\n"
"• Porto de Augas Negras: Cidade situada ao sur da Baía das Pérolas.\n"
"• Carcyn: Situada entre os Bosques Grises e o Gran Río.\n"
"• Dan’Tonk: A cidade máis grande de Wesnoth, situada no centro do país, "
"xusto ao oeste e ao norte de Weldyn.\n"
"• Soradoc: A cidade máis oriental de Wesnoth, controla a confluencia do río "
"Weldyn e o Gran Río.\n"
"• Forte Tahn: O posto fronteirizo máis meridional, controla a estrada norte/"
"sur que cruza o río Aethen.\n"
"• Tath: Importante cidade forte ao norte de Dan’Tonk, exerce control sobre a "
"rexión salvaxe arredor do leste dos Outeiros Pardos e ao norte ata o Vao de "
"Abez.\n"
"• Westin: Unha pequena pero importante cidade en Kerlath, a provincia máis "
"meridional de Wesnoth. Alí pódese atopar a antiga Cidadela de Westin.\n"
"• Southport: Unha pequena vila no extremo sur de Kerlath, preto da fraga "
"Negra."

#. [topic]: id=kingdom_wesnoth
#. Geography of Wesnoth
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:127
msgid ""
"<header>Notable land features:</header>\n"
"    • Gryphon Mountain: Home of the fabled Gryphons.\n"
"    • Ford of Abez: Shallow part of the Great River, it is usually "
"controlled by Wesnothian forces.\n"
"    • Weldyn River: It branches from the Great River and goes south.\n"
"    • Great Central Plain: Area bounded by Weldyn, Dan’Tonk, and Fort Tahn, "
"this plain is Wesnoth’s bread basket and home to most of its population.\n"
"    • Dulatus Hills: These rolling hills bordering the Great Central Plain "
"provide much of Wesnoth’s livestock and agriculture.\n"
"    • Brown Hills: Wasteland surrounding Gryphon Mountain that is not well-"
"populated and occasionally very dangerous.\n"
"    • Horse Plains: Region of rolling plains just south of the Great River, "
"bounded by Glyn’s Forest to the west and the River Weldyn to the east; the "
"southern reach merges into the Central Plain. Home of the powerful Horse "
"Clans; the best horses in Wesnoth are bred here.\n"
"    • Estmark Hills: Largish range rising south of the Great River and east "
"of the Weldyn River. The northernmost portion, nearest the River Weldyn, has "
"at various times been settled by Wesnothians, but the Kingdom’s control is "
"tenuous at best and banditry is common.\n"
"    • Glyn’s Forest: Sometimes known as the Royal Forest, named for one of "
"Haldric II’s sons.\n"
"    • Grey Woods: Large forest in the heart of the wilds of Wesnoth, located "
"between Carcyn and Aldril and generally considered to be haunted.\n"
"    • Isle of Alduin: An important island off the coast of Wesnoth home to "
"the Great Academy of Magic, where many of Wesnoth’s greatest mages were "
"trained.\n"
"    • Green Swamp: Large swamp on the banks of the Great River northeast of "
"the Grey Woods."
msgstr ""
"<header>Accidentes terrestres notables:</header>\n"
"• Alto dos Grifóns: Lar dos lendarios Grifóns.\n"
"• Vao de Abez: Parte pouco profunda do Gran Río, normalmente controlada "
"polas forzas do Noroeste.\n"
"• Río Güedin: Ramifícase desde o Gran Río e vai cara ao sur.\n"
"• Gran Chaira Central: Área delimitada por Güedin, Danton e o Forte de Tan, "
"esta chaira é o graneiro do Noroeste e o fogar da maior parte da súa "
"poboación.\n"
"• Picos de Dulatus: Estas ondulantes outeiros que bordean a Gran Chaira "
"Central proporcionan gran parte do gando e a agricultura do Noroeste.\n"
"• Serra Dourada: Terras baldías que rodean o alto Grifón, que non están ben "
"poboadas e ocasionalmente son moi perigosas.\n"
"• Chairas das bestas: Rexión de chairas ondulantes xusto ao sur do Gran Río, "
"delimitada pola fraga de Glin ao oeste e o Río Güedin ao leste; o tramo sur "
"fúndese coa Chaira Central. Lar dos poderosos Clans de Cabalos; os mellores "
"cabalos do Noroeste críanse aquí.\n"
"• Lombas de Ismar: Unha ampla cordilleira que se ergue ao sur do Gran Río e "
"ao leste do río Güedin. A parte máis setentrional, a máis próxima ao río "
"Güedin, foi poboada por habitantes do Noroeste en varias ocasións, pero o "
"control do Reino é, na mellor das hipóteses, tenue e o bandidaxe é común.\n"
"• Bosque de Glin: Ás veces coñecido como o Bosque Real, chamado así por un "
"dos fillos de Aldrico II.\n"
"• Bosques Grises: Gran fraga no corazón das terras salvaxes de Noroeste, "
"situado entre Corsin e Eildrin e xeralmente considerado como un lugar "
"encantado.\n"
"• Illa de Alduin: Unha illa importante fronte á costa de Noroeste, fogar da "
"Gran Academia de Maxia, onde se adestraron moitos dos mellores magos de "
"Noroeste.\n"
"• Pantano Verde: Gran pantano ás beiras do Gran Río ao nordeste dos Bosques "
"Grises."

#. [topic]: id=elensefar
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:144
msgid "Elensefar"
msgstr "Elensefar"

#. [topic]: id=elensefar
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:145
msgid ""
"Elensefar is at times a province of <ref dst='kingdom_wesnoth'>Wesnoth</"
"ref>, at times an independent country, and at times in a treaty federation "
"with Wesnoth. Its borders are the <ref dst='great_river'>Great River</ref> "
"to the north, a loosely defined line with Wesnoth to the east, the Bay of "
"Pearls to the south, and the <ref dst='great_ocean'>ocean</ref> to the west. "
"More information is found in the historical narrative of Wesnoth."
msgstr ""
"Elensefar é, segundo a época, unha provincia do <ref "
"dst='kingdom_wesnoth'>Reino do Noroeste</ref>, un país independente ou parte "
"dunha federación vinculada por tratados co Noroeste. Os seus límites están "
"marcados polo <ref dst='great_river'>Gran Río</ref> ao norte, unha liña mal "
"definida co Noroeste ao leste, a Baía das Perlas ao sur e o <ref "
"dst='great_ocean'>océano</ref> ao oeste. Pódese atopar máis información na "
"crónica histórica do Noroeste."

#. [topic]: id=elensefar
#. Geography of Elensefar area
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:149
msgid ""
"<header>Notable cities:</header>\n"
"    • Elensefar: The capital, located on an island in the Great River delta, "
"though some peripheral farmland extends slightly on both sides of the Great "
"River.\n"
"    • Carcyn: City on the Wesnoth–Elensefar border, disputed with Wesnoth."
msgstr ""
"<header>Cidades notables:</header>\n"
"• Elensefar: A capital, situada nunha illa no delta do Gran Río, aínda que "
"algunhas terras de cultivo periféricas se estenden lixeiramente a ambos os "
"dous lados do Gran Río.\n"
"• Carcyn: Cidade na fronteira entre o Noroeste e Elensefar, disputada con "
"Wesnoth."

#. [topic]: id=elensefar
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:154
msgid ""
"<header>Notable land features:</header>\n"
"    • <ref dst='great_river'>Great River</ref>: It is very wide at this "
"point, and only ships can cross it."
msgstr ""
"<header>Características terrestres notables:</header>\n"
"• <ref dst='great_river'>Gran Río</ref>: É moi ancho neste punto e só os "
"barcos poden cruzalo."

#. [topic]: id=northlands
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:160
msgid "Northlands"
msgstr "Terras Nórdicas"

#. [topic]: id=northlands
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:161
msgid ""
"The Northlands are filled with unstable clans in endless conflict. It is an "
"unlawful and perilous place plagued by its cold, icy terrain and constant "
"war. Various groups of orcs, dwarves, humans, gryphons, ogres, and even "
"elves fight over the region. The northern and eastern borders of the "
"Northlands are not defined, the southern border is the <ref "
"dst='great_river'>Great River</ref>, and the western border is the <ref "
"dst='great_ocean'>ocean</ref>.\n"
"\n"
"Yet despite the sheer wilderness above the Northlands, the subterranean "
"Dwarvish Kingdoms of Knalga and Kal Kartha are exceptions to their chaotic "
"surroundings, providing both heat and protection to their people. While they "
"may often be in conflict with orcs and trolls, the heart of Dwarvish "
"territory is considered relatively safe in comparison."
msgstr ""
"As Terras do Norte están cheas de clans inestables en conflito interminable. "
"É un lugar ilegal e perigoso, asolagado polo seu terreo frío e xeado e pola "
"guerra constante. Diversos grupos de orcos, ananos, humanos, grifos, ogros e "
"incluso elfos loitan pola rexión. As fronteiras norte e leste das Terras do "
"Norte non están definidas; a fronteira sur é o <ref dst='great_river'>Gran "
"Río</ref> e a fronteira oeste é o <ref dst='great_ocean'>oceano</ref>.\n"
"\n"
"Porén, a pesar da inmensa natureza salvaxe por riba das Terras do Norte, os "
"Reinos ananos subterráneos de Knalga e Kal Kartha son excepcións ao seu "
"contorno caótico, proporcionando tanto calor como protección ao seu pobo. "
"Aínda que a miúdo poidan estar en conflito con orcos e troles, o corazón do "
"territorio anano considérase relativamente seguro en comparación."

#. [topic]: id=northlands
#. Geography of the Northlands
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:167
msgid ""
"<header>Notable cities:</header>\n"
"    • Glamdrol: An Orcish tribal capital.\n"
"    • Wesmere: The location of the Ka’lian — the Elvish Council\n"
"    • Dwarven Doors: A mixed human/dwarven town in the region of Knalga in "
"the southern Heart Mountains. A major trade center.\n"
"    • Saurgrath: A former saurian capital in the Swamp of Dread.\n"
"    • Dallben and Delwyn: Human villages originally built by settlers who "
"crossed the Great River during Wesnoth’s Golden Age expansion. Now "
"abandoned. The forested area northeast of <ref dst='elensefar'>Elensefar</"
"ref>, where these villages were located, was named the Annuvin province by "
"men but was known by the elves as Wesmere."
msgstr ""
"<header>Cidades notables:</header>\n"
"• Glamdrol: Unha capital tribal orca.\n"
"• Wesmere: A localización dos Ka’lian — o Consello Élfico.\n"
"• Portas Ananas: Unha cidade mixta de humanos e ananos na rexión de Knalga, "
"no sur das Montañas Corazón. Un importante centro comercial.\n"
"• Saurgrath: Unha antiga capital sauria no Pantano do Pavor.\n"
"• Dallben e Delwyn: Aldeas humanas construídas orixinalmente por colonos que "
"cruzaron o Gran Río durante a expansión da Idade de Ouro do Noroeste. Agora "
"abandonadas. A zona boscosa ao nordeste de <ref dst='elensefar'>Elensefar</"
"ref>, onde se atopaban estas aldeas, foi chamada provincia de Annuvin polos "
"homes, pero era coñecida polos elfos como Wesmere."

#. [topic]: id=northlands
#. Geography of the Northlands
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:176
msgid ""
"<header>Notable land features:</header>\n"
"    • <ref dst='heart_mountains'>Heart Mountains</ref>: A virtually "
"impassable barrier between the river country and the Northern Plains.\n"
"    • Heartfangs: The particularly forbidding stretch of high peaks "
"southwest of Lake Vrug and north of the Forest of Wesmere. The most "
"inhospitable and dangerous portion of the Heart Mountains; only hermits, "
"madmen, and mages live there.\n"
"    • Swamp of Dread: A very large bog located between the Heart Mountains "
"and the Great River. A notoriously dangerous place.\n"
"    • Lake Vrug: A large mountain lake whose river carves the only pathway "
"through the Northern Mountains.\n"
"    • <ref dst='arkan_thoria'>Arkan-thoria</ref>: The river that comes out "
"of Lake Vrug. This is the elvish name; among humans it is called Longlier.\n"
"    • River Listra: The south-running tributary of the Great River into "
"which the Arkan-thoria empties.\n"
"    • Lintanir Forest: The southernmost portion of the Great Northern "
"Forest, a gigantic wood whose eastern and northern boundaries are known only "
"to the elves. Their capital, Elensiria, has only seldom been visited by "
"humans.\n"
"    • <ref dst='great_river'>Great River</ref>: The origin of this river is "
"somewhere in the east of the northern lands."
msgstr ""
"<header>Elementos xeográficos destacados:</header>\n"
"    • <ref dst='heart_mountains'>Montañas profundas</ref>: Unha barreira "
"practicamente infranqueable entre a terra fluvial e as Chairas do Norte.\n"
"    • Trabadas do Corazón: O tramo especialmente ameazante de picos elevados "
"ao suroeste do Lago Vrug e ao norte do Bosque de Wesmere. É a parte máis "
"inhóspita e perigosa das Montañas profundas; só ermitáns, tolos e magos "
"viven alí.\n"
"    • Pantano do Pavor: Unha enorme braña situada entre as Montañas "
"profundas e o Gran Río. Un lugar coñecido pola súa perigosidade.\n"
"    • Lagoa de Brugue: Un gran lago de montaña cuxo río escava o único paso "
"a través das Montañas do Norte. • <ref dst='arkan_thoria'>Arkan-thoria</"
"ref>: O río que sae do Lago Brugue. Este é o nome élfico; os humanos "
"chámanlle Longlier.\n"
"    • Río Listra: A afluente do Gran Río que flúe cara ao sur e no cal "
"desemboca o Arkan-thoria. \n"
"    • Bosque de Lintanir: A parte máis meridional do Gran Bosque do Norte, "
"unha masa forestal xigantesca cuxos límites orientais e setentrionais só son "
"coñecidos polos elfos. A súa capital, Elensiria, foi raramente visitada por "
"humanos.\n"
"    • <ref dst='great_river'>Gran Río</ref>: A orixe deste río atópase "
"nalgún punto ao leste das terras do norte."

#. [topic]: id=southwest_elven_lands
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:189
msgid "Southwest Elven Lands"
msgstr "Terras dos Elfos do Sur"

#. [topic]: id=southwest_elven_lands
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:190
msgid ""
"The Wood Elves are separate from those of the north, and have only "
"intermittent relations with them and most other countries. Its borders are "
"the <ref dst='great_ocean'>ocean</ref> to the west, the Black River to the "
"south and southeast, the lands of Wesnoth to the north and the Kerlath "
"province to the east."
msgstr ""
"Os Elfos do Bosque están separados dos do norte e só manteñen relacións "
"intermitentes con eles e coa maioría dos outros países. As súas fronteiras "
"son o <ref dst='great_ocean'>oceano</ref> ao oeste, o Río Negro ao sur e "
"sureste, as terras do Noroeste ao norte e a provincia de Kerlath ao leste."

#. [topic]: id=southwest_elven_lands
#. Geography of the Southwest
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:194
msgid ""
"<header>Notable land features:</header>\n"
"    • Aethenwood: The largest southern forest, home to reclusive <ref dst='.."
"race_elf'>elves</ref>.\n"
"    • Vale of Blossoming Trees: An elvish vale at the southern edge of the "
"Aethenwood. It contains the sacred Isle of Elrath.\n"
"    • Lake Aelin: An elvish lake at the edge of their territory along the "
"River Aethen.\n"
"    • Black Forest: An ancient and likely haunted forest of which very "
"little is known, believed to have been once inhabited by elves. Those who "
"enter it seldom return."
msgstr ""
"<header>Características terrestres notables:</header>\n"
"• Fraga de Aethen: A maior fraga do sur, fogar dos reclusos <ref dst='.."
"race_elf'>elfos</ref>.\n"
"• Val das Árbores Floridas: un val élfico na beira sur da fraga de Aethen. "
"Contén a sagrada Illa de Elrath.\n"
"• Lago Aelin: un lago élfico na beira do seu territorio ao longo do río "
"Aethen.\n"
"• Fraga Negra: unha fraga antiga e probablemente encantada da que se sabe "
"moi pouco, crese que foi habitada noutro tempo por elfos. Os que entran nel "
"raramente regresan."

#. [topic]: id=heart_mountains
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:203
msgid "Heart Mountains"
msgstr "Montañas Profundas"

#. [topic]: id=heart_mountains
#. The Whitefang Clan’s primary description is in DiD
#. Wesnoth 1.9.4 added Haggid-Dargor to the encyclopedia, but it has no other mention in mainline
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:206
msgid ""
"A virtually impassable barrier between the <ref dst='arkan_thoria'>river</"
"ref> country and the <ref dst='far_north'>Northern Plains</ref>. The local "
"orcs call them the Haggid-Dargor. The powerful Whitefang Clan in the region "
"is named after the eastern edge of the mountains, which they call the "
"Whitefang Mountains for their distinctive shape."
msgstr ""
"Unha barreira case infranqueable entre a rexión do <ref "
"dst='arkan_thoria'>río</ref> e as <ref dst='far_north'>chairas do Norte</"
"ref>. Os orcos locais chámanlles Haggid-Dargor. O poderoso Clan Whitefang da "
"rexión recibe o seu nome do borde oriental das montañas, que eles denominan "
"Montañas Whitefang pola súa forma distintiva."

#. [topic]: id=far_north
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:211
msgid "Far North"
msgstr "Chairas Nórdicas"

#. [topic]: id=far_north
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:212
msgid ""
"Cold, harsh, and inaccessible, the Far North is the ancestral home of the "
"Orcish Clannate. It lies north of the <ref dst='heart_mountains'>Heart "
"Mountains</ref>, which the Orcs call the Haggid-Dargor and claim (without "
"merit) as their own. To the east lie the Unaligned Tribes of the Wild "
"Steppe, who fell out of the control of the Clannate, instead roaming with "
"wild human barbarians and clashing with the High Elves of the North Plains "
"(known as North Elves in human lands). The High Elves themselves reside "
"further east, where it is rumored they rule a vast kingdom."
msgstr ""
"Cunhas duras condicións climáticas e de difícil acceso, as Chairas Nórdicas "
"son o fogar ancestral dos clans dos orcos. Están situadas ao norte das <ref "
"dst='heart_mountains'>Montañas Profundas'</ref>, que or orcos chaman Haggid-"
"Dargor e reclaman (de modo ilexítimo) como súas. Ao leste están as tribos "
"independentes da Estepa Salvaxe, fóra do control dos clans, e habitadas por "
"humanos bárbaros. Estas á súa vez limitan co territorio dos elfos das "
"Chairas Nórdicas (popularmente coñecidos como «elfos do norte»). Os elfos do "
"norte viven lonxe ao leste, onde se rumorea teñen un gran reino."

#. [topic]: id=far_north
#. Geography of the Far North
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:216
msgid ""
"<header>Notable cities:</header>\n"
"    • Barag Gor: A city home to the Orcish Council.\n"
"    • Bitok\n"
"    • Borstep\n"
"    • Farzi\n"
"    • Jotha: A large fortified capital of the local merfolk south of Bitok.\n"
"    • Lmarig\n"
"    • Melmog\n"
"    • Prestim\n"
"    • Tirigaz: A coastal orcish town that occasionally raids Jotha.\n"
"    • Dorest: The northernmost human city.\n"
"    • Arcanclave Citadel: A mythical fortress far beyond the woods of "
"Lintanir, believed to have been forged by an earth elemental in the midst of "
"battle. Its ruins have now become a military stronghold.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"<header>Cidades notables:</header>\n"
"    • Barag Gor: Unha cidade que alberga o Consello Orco.\n"
"    • Bitok\n"
"    • Borstep\n"
"    • Farzi\n"
"    • Jotha: Unha gran capital fortificada dos sirénidos locais ao sur de "
"Bitok.\n"
"    • Lmarig\n"
"    • Melmog\n"
"    • Prestim\n"
"    • Tirigaz: Unha cidade orca costeira que ocasionalmente ataca Jotha.\n"
"    • Dorest: A cidade humana máis setentrional.\n"
"    • Cidadela de Arcanclave: Unha fortaleza mítica moito máis alá das "
"fragas de Lintanir, que se cre que foi forxada por un elemental da terra no "
"medio dunha batalla. As súas ruínas convertéronse agora nunha fortaleza "
"militar.\n"
"    "

#. [topic]: id=far_north
#. Geography of the Far North
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:232
msgid ""
"<header>Notable land features:</header>\n"
"    • Desert of Death: An unusually dry desert in the Far North filled with "
"venomous Sand Scuttlers. It is extremely hot by day yet chilly by night.\n"
"    • Black Marshes: A perilous swamp north of Tirigaz filled with violent "
"monsters.\n"
"    • Mountains of Dorth: A set of mountains north of the Heart Mountains. "
"Though nowhere near as dangerous as its southern neighbour, it is "
"nonetheless deadly to inexperienced travelers.\n"
"    • Mountains of Haag: A group of high mountains inhabited by groups of "
"orcs, trolls and dwarves.\n"
"    • Mourned Hills: A series of rolling hills stretching south from the "
"Mountains of Haag. The orcish town of Lmarig is at the southern edge of "
"these hills.\n"
"    • Greenwood: An elvish forest located near the Lintanir Forest. Some say "
"it was once connected to it, until groups of savage orcs burned much of the "
"forest.\n"
"    • Silent Forest: A dense forest inhabited by a few elves, once known as "
"Gitamoth.\n"
"    • Forest of Thelien: A dense coniferous forest sometimes inhabited by "
"elves.\n"
"    • River Oumph: A river flowing from the Mountains of Haag to its delta "
"just south of Bitok.\n"
"    • River Bork: A river of the Far North flowing from a lake next to the "
"Mourned Hills.\n"
"    • Frosty Wastes: A cold, snowy desert in the far north inhabited only by "
"the occasional monster.\n"
"    • Barren Plains: A vast, sparsely populated snowy tundra."
msgstr ""
"<header>Caracteristicas terrestres notables:</header>\n"
"• Deserto da Morte: Un deserto inusualmente seco no Extremo Norte cheo de "
"velenosos Escorregadores de Area. É extremadamente quente de día pero frío "
"de noite.\n"
"• Marismas Negras: Un perigoso pantano ao norte de Tirigaz cheo de monstros "
"violentos.\n"
"• Montañas de Dorth: Un conxunto de montañas ao norte das Montañas do "
"Corazón. Aínda que non é tan perigoso como o seu veciño do sur, non deixa de "
"ser mortal para os viaxeiros inexpertos.\n"
"• Montañas de Haag: Un grupo de montañas altas habitadas por grupos de "
"orcos, troles e ananos.\n"
"• Outeiros de Loito: Unha serie de outeiros ondulados que se estenden cara "
"ao sur desde as Montañas de Haag. A vila orca de Lmarig está no límite sur "
"destes outeiros.\n"
"• Fraga Verde: Unha fraga élfica situada preto da fraga de Lintanir. Algúns "
"din que outrora estivo conectada a ela, ata que grupos de orcos salvaxes "
"queimaron gran parte da fraga.\n"
"• Fraga Acalada: Unha densa fraga habitada por uns poucos elfos, outrora "
"coñecida como Gitamoth. \n"
"• fraga de Thelien: Unha densa fraga de coníferas ás veces habitado por "
"elfos.\n"
"• Río Oumph: Un río que flúe desde as montañas de Haag ata o seu delta xusto "
"ao sur de Bitok.\n"
"• Río Bork: Un río do extremo norte que flúe desde un lago xunto aos "
"outeiros de loito.\n"
"• Ermos xeados: Un deserto frío e nevado no extremo norte habitado só por "
"algún monstro ocasional.\n"
"• Chairas áridas: Unha vasta tundra nevada escasamente poboada."

#. [topic]: id=far_south
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:249
msgid "Far South"
msgstr "Lonxano Sur"

#. [topic]: id=far_south
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:250
msgid ""
"A vast region south of Kerlath home to many mysterious races, including jinn "
"and wyverns. Very little is known for certain about what lies here."
msgstr ""
"Unha vasta rexión ao sur de Kerlath que acolle moitas razas misteriosas, "
"incluíndo xinns e vívernas. Moi pouco se sabe con certeza sobre o que hai "
"aquí."

#. [topic]: id=far_south
#. Geography of the Far South
#: data/core/encyclopedia/geography.cfg:254
msgid ""
"<header>Notable land features:</header>\n"
"    • Mountains of Peril: A tall and deadly mountain range in the Far South "
"inhabited by bands of vicious barbarians and monsters.\n"
"    • Sandy Wastes: A hot desert located southeast of Kerlath. It is "
"considered an impassable barrier by Wesnothians, filled with very sparse "
"vegetation consisting of no more than a few shrubs and cacti.\n"
"    • Isanbar: A mysterious mountain in the Sandy Wastes, surrounded "
"entirely by flat desert. It is not part of any mountain range and its "
"existence is doubted by many.\n"
"    • Ashland Desert: A mysterious desert rumored to exist beyond even the "
"remote Sandy Wastes, sometimes known simply as the Ashland. A far-off "
"civilization is sometimes said to live around the desert."
msgstr ""
"<header>Caracteristicas terrestres notables:</header>\n"
"• Montañas do Perigo: Unha cadea montañosa alta e mortal no Extremo Sur, "
"habitada por bandas de bárbaros e monstros feroces.\n"
"• Ermos Areosos: Un deserto cálido situado ao sueste de Kerlath. Os "
"habitantes do Noroeste considérano unha barreira infranqueable, cheo de "
"vexetación moi escasa que non consiste máis que nuns poucos arbustos e "
"cactos.\n"
"• Isanbar: Unha montaña misteriosa nos Ermos Areosos, completamente rodeada "
"por deserto plano. Non forma parte de ningunha cadea montañosa e moitos "
"dubidan da súa existencia.\n"
"• Deserto de Ashland: Un deserto misterioso que se di que existe máis aló "
"dos afastados Ermos Areosos, ás veces coñecido simplemente como Ashland. "
"Dicíase que unha civilización afastada vive ao redor deste deserto."

